org.batfish.datamodel.acl.normalize

Class AclToAclLineMatchExpr

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.batfish.datamodel.acl.normalize.AclToAclLineMatchExpr
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GenericAclLineMatchExprVisitor<AclLineMatchExpr>

    public final class AclToAclLineMatchExpr
extends Object
implements GenericAclLineMatchExprVisitor<AclLineMatchExpr>
    Reduce an IpAccessList to a single AclLineMatchExpr.

    All references to other ACLs are inlined. For each LineAction.PERMIT line, we generate an expression of the form "matches that line AND does not match any earlier LineAction.DENY line". We then combine all those expressions into a single OrMatchExpr. Note that the line expressions may overlap. This is OK because we are only trying to express the space of the entire ACL as an AclLineMatchExpr. If you're interested in an AclLineMatchExpr that describes exactly what is matched by a particular line, you want something of the form "matches that line AND does not match ANY early line (LineAction.PERMIT or LineAction.DENY)". This class does not do that.

    We use BDDs to keep the expressions small. This refines the generated line expressions to the form "matches that line AND does not match any early OVERLAPPING LineAction.DENY line".
